==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proclivity
<hw>Pro*cliv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proclivitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>proclivit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclination; propensity; proneness; tendency.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>proclivity</xex> to steal.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Abp.
Bramhall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Readiness; facility; aptitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had such a dexterous <qex>proclivity</qex> as his teachers were
fain to restrain his forwardness.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H.
Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proclivous</ent>⟦br⟧
